node.text:
Whether you're a new mom, an expecting mom, a mom of two or more children, or can’t become/decided against becoming a mother and are therefore celebrating your own mother today -  we wish you a HAPPY MOTHER'S DAY!

It is a crazy and demanding but wonderful journey and very unique for every single mother. This is why we asked Jennifer, our brand ambassador, to share with us her thoughts and memories about her first months of being a mom. We want to invite all of you to share your thoughts as well! 

How has your life changed? 
What would you say to the moms to be and the ones considering becoming a mom?

@thejeneralist: "Becoming a mother is one of the craziest things you can do in life. It's a selfless act of love that requires you to temporarily put aside you own needs and place that focus on somebody else.
You learn quickly to adjust to the roller coaster of emotions that are full of each day, reminding yourself to cherish each passing moment.
You become a student all over again as your child becomes your greatest teacher. And in the same breath your greatest friendship.
Becoming a mother has been the greatest challenge I've faced in life but it's also been the most rewarding experience I've been privileged to have." 

#mothersday #mom #momtobe #momtobeagain #momslifebelike

How do we keep children entertained while they wait? ✈🙌
⁠
Waiting times, especially at the airport or right before an exciting trip, can be challenging, for you, but even more for your little ones. ⁠
⁠With our colleagues from @jetkidscom we have some true travel experts on board who collected some ideas to keep kids happy during that time!

Swipe to see our tips and feel free to share yours in the comments section!

#jetkidsbystokkebedbox #travelwithkids #familytravel #travelhacks

Photo by Stokke on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIPS FOR WAITING TIMES WITH CHILDREN 1. Play some old-school paper games or cards together, or make use of activity books They take little space, and you can fit them inside the BedBox or Crew BackPack. Bringing coloring books and crayons or a notebook to doodle or play tic-tac-toe or UNO, an old-time family favorite that is sold everywhere!'.

Photo by Stokke on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIPS TIPS FOR WAITING TIMES WITH CHILDREN 2: Offer some snacks. A hungry child is a grumpy child (sure, you know this). Keeping a few snacks in your purse for unexpected waits is a great way to improve your child's state of mind and pass the time.'.

Photo by Stokke on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIPS FOR WAITING TIMES WITH CHILDREN 3: Make use of your environment. An airport or train station might not sound like thrilling surrounds for children. If you're stuck at the airport due to a delayed flight, walk around and check the shops or watch planes taking off and landing. Children love riding the BedBox around, and this is the perfect time to let them enjoy this'.

Photo by Stokke on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIPS FOR WAITING TIMES WITH CHILDREN 4: Have a "Treasure Hunt". All you need is a magazine and a little creativity. Flip through the pages and have your children find a certain item or image that you saw.'.

Photo by Stokke on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIPS FOR WAITING TIMES WITH CHILDREN 5: Embrace technology. An iPad, Kindle, and smartphone are the "top go-to boredom busters" for keeping children entertained. You do not have to feel guilty. It is a special situation that justifies a potentially higher screen time than the usual one. Many (if not all) airports nowadays offer free wifi, a great benefit for this!'.
